[Name] Festival
[Summary] A general multi-lingual speech synthesis system.
[License] MIT/X Consortium License
[Description] Festival is a general multi-lingual speech synthesis system developed at CSTR. It offers a full text to speech system with various APIs, as well an environment for development and research of speech synthesis techniques. It is written in C++ with a Scheme-based command interpreter for general control.
[Homepage] http://www.cstr.ed.ac.uk/projects/festival/
